President Obama expresses his deep sadness over the death of Lee Kuan Yew, Singapore's Minister Mentor. He offers his condolences to the Lee family and the people of Singapore. President Obama praises Lee Kuan Yew as a visionary leader who transformed Singapore into one of the world's most prosperous countries. He acknowledges Lee's respected views on Asian dynamics and economic management, and mentions seeking his advice on governance and development. President Obama personally values the wisdom shared by Lee during his visit to Singapore in 2009, which helped shape his policy of rebalancing to the Asia Pacific. He recognizes Lee as a historic figure and the father of modern Singapore, as well as a great strategist in Asian affairs.